description: The Chrome Management API is a suite of services that allows Chrome administrators to view, manage and gain insights on their Chrome OS and Chrome Browser devices.
name: chromemanagement

https://www.googleapis.com/auth/chrome.m.description: See detailed information about apps installed on Chrome browsers and devices managed by your organization
See basic device and telemetry information collected from Chrome OS devices or users managed within your organization
See reports about devices and Chrome browsers managed within your organization

appId.description: Output only. Unique identifier of the app. For Chrome apps and extensions, the 32-character id (e.g. ehoadneljpdggcbbknedodolkkjodefl). For Android apps, the package name (e.g. com.evernote).

description.description: Output only. Description of the installed app.

permissions.description: Output only. Permissions of the installed app.

displayName.description: Output only. Name of the installed app.

homepageUri.description: Output only. Homepage uri of the installed app.

osUserCount.description: Output only. Count of ChromeOS users with this app installed.

appSource.description: Output only. Source of the installed app.
enumDescriptions: Generally for extensions and Chrome apps.

browserDeviceCount.description: Output only. Count of browser devices with this app installed.

disabled.description: Output only. Whether the app is disabled.

appType.description: Output only. Type of the app.

appInstallType.description: Output only. How the app was installed.

GoogleChromeManagementV1CountChromeDevic.description: Response containing a list of devices expiring in each month of a selected time frame. Counts are grouped by model and Auto Update Expiration date.

deviceAueCountReports.description: The list of reports sorted by auto update expiration date in ascending order.

code.description: The status code, which should be an enum value of google.rpc.Code.

additionalProperties.description: Properties of the object. Contains field @type with type URL.

details.description: A list of messages that carry the error details. There is a common set of message types for APIs to use.

message.description: A developer-facing error message, which should be in English. Any user-facing error message should be localized and sent in the google.rpc.Status.details field, or localized by the client.

GoogleRpcStatus.description: The `Status` type defines a logical error model that is suitable for different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs. It is used by [gRPC](https://github.com/grpc). Each `Status` message contains three pieces of data: error code, error message, and error details. You can find out more about this error model and how to work with it in the [API Design Guide](https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/errors).

reportTime.description: Output only. Time at which the graphics data was reported.

displays.description: Output only. Information about the displays for the device.

connectionState.description: Output only. Current connection state of the network.
enumDescriptions: The network is connected and internet connectivity is available.
The network is connected and not in a detected portal state, but internet connectivity may not be available.
The network is connected but a portal state was detected. Internet connectivity may be limited.
The network is in the process of connecting.

wifiPowerManagementEnabled.description: Output only. Wifi power management enabled

encryptionOn.description: Output only. Whether the wifi encryption key is turned off.

wifiLinkQuality.description: Output only. Wifi link quality. Value ranges from [0, 70]. 0 indicates no signal and 70 indicates a strong signal.

transmissionPowerDbm.description: Output only. Transmission power measured in decibels.

transmissionBitRateMbps.description: Output only. Transmission bit rate measured in Megabits per second.

designMinVoltage.description: Output only. Designed minimum output voltage (mV)

manufactureDate.description: Output only. The date the battery was manufactured.

technology.description: Output only. Technology of the battery. Example: Li-ion

httpsLatencyData.description: Output only. HTTPS latency test data.

GoogleChromeManagementV1NetworkDiagnosti.description: Network testing results to determine the health of the device's network connection, for example whether the HTTPS latency is high or normal.

totalDiskBytes.description: The total space for user data storage in the device in bytes.

availableDiskBytes.description: The available space for user data storage in the device in bytes.

updateState.description: Output only. Current state of the os update.
enumDescriptions: OS has started download on device.
Device needs reboot to finish upload.

It is only set when update status is OS_IMAGE_DOWNLOAD_IN_PROGRESS or OS_UPDATE_NEED_REBOOT. Note this could be a dummy "0.0.0.0" for OS_UPDATE_NEED_REBOOT status for some edge cases, e.g. update engine is restarted without a reboot.

securityLevel.description: Security level of the Thunderbolt bus.
enumDescriptions: Thunderbolt security level is not set.
All devices are automatically connected by the firmware. No user approval is needed.
User is asked whether the device is allowed to be connected.
User is asked whether the device is allowed to be connected. In addition the device is sent a challenge that should match the expected one based on a random key written to the key sysfs attribute
The firmware automatically creates tunnels for Thunderbolt.
The firmware automatically creates tunnels for the USB controller and Display Port in a dock. All PCIe links downstream of the dock are removed.

isTheme.description: Output only. Whether the app or extension is a theme.

kioskEnabled.description: Output only. Whether this app is enabled for Kiosk mode on ChromeOS devices

GoogleTypeDate.description: Represents a whole or partial calendar date, such as a birthday. The time of day and time zone are either specified elsewhere or are insignificant. The date is relative to the Gregorian Calendar. This can represent one of the following: * A full date, with non-zero year, month, and day values. * A month and day, with a zero year (for example, an anniversary). * A year on its own, with a zero month and a zero day. * A year and month, with a zero day (for example, a credit card expiration date). Related types: * google.type.TimeOfDay * google.type.DateTime * google.protobuf.Timestamp

day.description: Day of a month. Must be from 1 to 31 and valid for the year and month, or 0 to specify a year by itself or a year and month where the day isn't significant.

year.description: Year of the date. Must be from 1 to 9999, or 0 to specify a date without a year.

month.description: Month of a year. Must be from 1 to 12, or 0 to specify a year without a month and day.
